message.content:
1. The tests showed no significant differences between the supplementation groups.
2. There were some gender differences in the test results.
3. Girls displayed higher scores than boys on the Wechsler Preschool and Primary Scale of Intelligence (WPPSI) Verbal IQ sentences subtest.
4. Girls scored higher than boys on the Day-Night cognitive test.
5. Girls scored higher than boys on the Brief Infant-Toddler Social Emotional Assessment (BITSEA) social competency.
6. Boys scored higher than girls in problem behaviour.
